{{Infobox power station |name = Asnæs Power Station |image = Asnæsværket (Kalundborg, Denmark).JPG |image_caption = The Asnæs Power Station |location_map = Denmark |location_map_caption= Location of Asnæs Power Station within Denmark |country = [[Denmark]] |location = [[Kalundborg]] | coordinates = {{coord|55|39|40.7|N|11|04|44.2|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |owner = [[DONG Energy]] |status = Operational |th_fuel_primary = [[Coal]] |th_fuel_tertiary = Fuel oil |th_combined_cycle = |ps_electrical_capacity= 1,057&nbsp;MW |commissioned = 1959 |decommissioned = }}
The '''Asnæs Power Station''' ({{lang-da|Asnæsværket}}) is a coal-fired power plant operated by [[DONG Energy]] in [[Kalundborg]], [[Denmark]]. It consists of three active units, which deliver 147&nbsp;MW (Unit 2), 270&nbsp;MW (Unit 4) and 640&nbsp;MW (Unit 5). Unit 3 went in service in 1959 and uses a {{convert|152.1|m|ft|adj=mid|-tall}} [[flue gas stack]], while Unit 5, which went into service in 1981, uses a {{convert|220.1|m|ft|adj=mid|-tall}} flue gas stack, the third tallest in Denmark. Its two 60m high coal cranes were dismantled in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dongenergy.com/en/media/newsroom/news/articles/giant-coal-cranes-to-be-decommissioned-at-asn%C3%A6s-power-station |title=Giant coal cranes to be decommissioned at Asnæs Power Station|publisher=[[DONG Energy]] |date=26 October 2016|accessdate=24 November 2016}}</ref>
