'''Katie Patrick''' (born 14 October 1980) is an [[Australia]]n environmental [[spokesperson]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/catapult/stories/s1797961.htm|title=Directing the green wave - Success Stories - Catapult - ABC Online|publisher=}}</ref> She is most known for her work founding The Green Pages, Australia's first online and published green business directory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thegreenpages.com.au/|title=The Green Pages Outdoor Group Fitness Training|publisher=}}</ref>

==Background==
Patrick was raised on Victoria's [[Mornington Peninsula]] and studied [[Environmental engineering|Environmental Engineering]] at [[Griffith University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/environment/sex-and-sustainability/2008/05/06/1209839649588.html|title=The Sydney Morning Herald: national, world, business, entertainment, sport and technology news from Australia's leading newspaper.|publisher=}}</ref>

At the age of 24 Patrick founded The Green Pages, Australia's first Green business directory.<ref>http://digitaledition.wentworthcourier.com.au/default.aspx?iid=8265&startpage=page0000006</ref> She has received several business awards including [[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]] woman of the year award for the [[entrepreneur]] category,<ref>http://www.cosmopolitan.com.au/fun_fearless_party.htm</ref> Australian Anthill 30under30 Award<ref>http://anthillonline.com/30under30-the-winners-part-4/</ref> and Smart Company 30-under-30 awards.<ref>http://www.smartcompany.com.au/hot-30-under-30-2009/katie-patrick.html</ref> Katie Patrick is also a proponent of [[eco fashion]] in Australia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/404|title=404 Page Not Found|publisher=}}</ref>

